title: Cristiano Ronaldo warns girlfriend Georgina Rodriguez’s male friend to ‘be careful’ after Instagram picture
text:
RON YOUR HEAD BE IT! Cristiano Ronaldo warns girlfriend Georgina Rodriguez’s male friend to ‘be careful’ after Instagram picture 
Stunner Rodriguez posted snap with male friend... but has the Real Madrid star taken exception or was he joking in comment? By Fred Nathan Comments CRISTIANO RONALDO has “threatened” a male friend of his gorgeous girlfriend Georgina Rodriguez on Instagram. 
The 21-year-old Spanish beauty posted a snap on her Instagram next to a pal called Callados – and it appears to be widely accepted that the duo are just good friends. 3

But it appears the Real Madrid ace is not too happy about his squeeze spending time with other men, posting “Cuidado” in the comments – meaning “be careful” in Spanish. 
But Ronaldo did add three laughing emojis with his comment – so we think he is probably taking the whole thing in jest. EPA Ronaldo is now going out with Spanish stunner Georgina Rodriguez

In November, the pair were snapped walking around Disneyland Paris arm-in-arm and publicly showing their affection for one another. 
And despite putting on a disguise, the Italian magazine Chi were able to identify the Portuguese international footballer as he cuddled up to his new love interest. 
Rodriguez worked at a Gucci store in the Spanish capital of Madrid and it is believed she caught the eye of the 32-year-old forward while in the VIP area of a Dolce & Gabbana event. 
The loved up pair have even been on a ski trip together – although they were forced to cut it short when the Real Madrid superstar injured his wrist. Cristiano Ronaldo shows off his CR7 underwear range and then goes crazy at the camera AP:Associated Press 3 Georgina Rodriguez is from Madrid and began dating Ronaldo last year 
It has not been ideal either on the pitch for Ronaldo this week, with Real having been beaten 2-1 at Valencia on Wednesday night in La Liga despite him scoring. 
It means Barcelona are just a point behind Real in the table - but Madrid have a game in hand.
